                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/1498: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-02-22T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >February 22, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 22—7:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>122. The German Chargé told me that he called this morning on the Minister of
                    Foreign Affairs<note n="89" xml:id="d427fn89">Koki Hirota.</note> and stated,
                    under instructions from his Government, that Germany will recognize
                    Manchukuo.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Shanghai for Hankow and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
